    "text": "Has anyone checked this out? <https://www.cs.cornell.edu/courses/cs6120/2023fa/self-guided/|CS 6120: Advanced Compilers: The Self-Guided Online Course>\n\n&gt; It covers universal compilers topics like intermediate representations, data flow, and “classic” optimizations as well as more research-flavored topics such as parallelization, just-in-time compilation, and garbage collection. The work consists of reading papers and open-source hacking tasks, which use <https://llvm.org/|LLVM> and <https://capra.cs.cornell.edu/bril/|an educational IR invented just for this class>.",
